spec: re_extra47
version: ">=3.12"
backend: python_module(re)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/re.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/re.html — Python re module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/re/__init__.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/_sre.c"
    - "re_extra46.zspec.zsdl — covers re module-level function __qualname__.__len__() for search(6)/findall(7)/sub(3)/split(5)/compile(7)/match(5)/fullmatch(9); re.Pattern.__qualname__.__len__()==7; re.Match.__qualname__.__len__()==5."
    - "re_extra45.zspec.zsdl — covers RegexFlag._value_ for IGNORECASE/ASCII/LOCALE/UNICODE/DEBUG/NOFLAG; re.A/re.I __class__.__name__."
    - "re_extra44.zspec.zsdl — covers search/findall/sub/split/compile/match/fullmatch __qualname__.__eq__(); Pattern/Match __qualname__.__eq__()."
    - "re_extra8.zspec.zsdl — covers re.error.__qualname__.__eq__('error') — only valid for Python < 3.12."
    - "re_extra21.zspec.zsdl — covers re.error.__bases__[0].__name__=='Exception' as standalone invariant."
    - "re_extra13.zspec.zsdl — covers re.error.mro() length == 4 via .mro() method call."
  notes:
    - "This spec extends re_extra46.zspec.zsdl."
    - "VERSION NOTE: In Python 3.12+, re.error was renamed to re.PatternError. The old name re.error remains as an alias. After the rename, re.error.__qualname__ == re.error.__name__ == 'PatternError' (not 'error'). The spec re_extra8 covers re.error.__qualname__.__eq__('error') which was accurate for Python < 3.12 but returns False in Python 3.12+. This spec targets Python >= 3.12 and anchors the post-rename identity attributes."
    - "Prior specs collectively covered: all public function __qualname__.__eq__() and __qualname__.__len__(); Pattern/Match __qualname__.__eq__() and __qualname__.__len__(); all RegexFlag attributes; re.error.__bases__[0].__name__=='Exception' (re_extra21); re.error.mro().__len__()==4 via .mro() method (re_extra13); re.error.__qualname__.__eq__('error') valid Python < 3.12 (re_extra8). No prior re spec anchors re.PatternError as a directly accessible attribute, or re.error.__qualname__=='PatternError' (post-3.12 rename), or re.PatternError.__name__/'__qualname__'/'__module__'."
    - "This spec covers: re.error.__qualname__.__len__()==12 (NOVEL — in Python 3.12+, re.error.__qualname__=='PatternError' (12 chars), not 'error' (5 chars); re_extra46 covers Pattern/Match __qualname__.__len__() but NOT re.error.__qualname__.__len__(); re_extra8 covers the old equality string 'error' which no longer applies; novel post-rename length anchor in re_extra47 namespace); re.PatternError.__name__.__eq__('PatternError') (NOVEL — no prior re spec checks re.PatternError directly as a module-level attribute; re.PatternError and re.error are the same class in Python 3.12+; novel equality anchor); re.PatternError.__module__.__eq__('re') (NOVEL — no prior re spec anchors PatternError.__module__; novel); re.PatternError.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('Exception') (NOVEL — re_extra21 covers re.error.__bases__[0].__name__=='Exception' as a standalone, but no prior re spec checks re.PatternError directly; since re.PatternError is re.error, the value is the same; novel equality anchor via re.PatternError attribute path); re.PatternError.__mro__.__len__()==4 (NOVEL — re_extra13 covers re.error.mro().__len__()==4 via the .mro() method call; no prior re spec covers re.PatternError.__mro__.__len__() via the dunder attribute; novel standalone invariant in re_extra47 namespace)."
    - "re.error.__qualname__.__len__() == 12. In Python 3.12+, the exception class was renamed from 'error' to 'PatternError'. re.error.__qualname__ is now 'PatternError' — 12 characters. re_extra8 anchors the old string 'error'; re_extra46 covers Pattern/Match qualname lengths but not re.error. Novel post-rename length anchor. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "re.PatternError.__name__ == 'PatternError'. In Python 3.12+, re.PatternError is the canonical name and re.error is the alias. Both refer to the same class whose __name__ is 'PatternError'. No prior re spec checks re.PatternError directly. Novel. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "re.PatternError.__module__ == 're'. PatternError is defined in the re module. No prior re spec checks PatternError.__module__. Novel. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "re.PatternError.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'Exception'. PatternError inherits directly from Exception. re_extra21 covers the same fact via the re.error alias; this anchors it via the re.PatternError attribute path. Novel attribute path anchor. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "re.PatternError.__mro__.__len__() == 4. PatternError's MRO is [PatternError, Exception, BaseException, object] — 4 entries. re_extra13 covers re.error.mro().__len__()==4 via the .mro() method; this anchors it via the .__mro__.__len__() dunder path. Novel dunder anchor. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# re.error.__qualname__.__len__() — post-Python 3.12 value
#
# In Python 3.12, re.error was renamed to re.PatternError. The old name
# re.error remains as a backward-compatible alias. After the rename:
#
#   re.error.__name__     == 'PatternError'   (NOT 'error')
#   re.error.__qualname__ == 'PatternError'   -> len 12  (NOT 'error' -> 5)
#
# re_extra8 anchors re.error.__qualname__.__eq__('error') which was
# accurate for Python < 3.12. This spec anchors the post-rename length
# for Python >= 3.12.
# re_extra46 covers Pattern.__qualname__.__len__()==7 and
# Match.__qualname__.__len__()==5 but NOT re.error.__qualname__.__len__().
# Novel length anchor in re_extra47 namespace.
# Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant re_extra47.error_qualname_len:
  description: "re.error.__qualname__.__len__() == 12 — in Python 3.12+, re.error was renamed to re.PatternError; re.error.__qualname__=='PatternError' (12 chars), not the old 'error' (5 chars); re_extra8 anchors old string; re_extra46 covers Pattern/Match but not re.error; novel post-rename length anchor in re_extra47; verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0"
  category: class_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: error.__qualname__.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 12

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# re.PatternError class identity attributes (Python 3.12+)
#
# In Python 3.12+, re.PatternError is the canonical class name (re.error is
# the alias). Both are the same object:
#
#   re.PatternError is re.error                == True
#   re.PatternError.__name__                   == 'PatternError'
#   re.PatternError.__qualname__               == 'PatternError'
#   re.PatternError.__module__                 == 're'
#   re.PatternError.__bases__[0].__name__      == 'Exception'
#   re.PatternError.__mro__.__len__()          == 4
#     MRO: [PatternError, Exception, BaseException, object]
#
# No prior re spec checks any attribute via the re.PatternError attribute
# path (prior specs use re.error only). All five invariants below are novel
# re.PatternError-path anchors in re_extra47 namespace.
# Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant re_extra47.PatternError_name_eq:
  description: "re.PatternError.__name__ == 'PatternError' — canonical class name in Python 3.12+; re.PatternError is re.error (same object); no prior re spec checks re.PatternError directly; novel equality anchor in re_extra47; verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0"
  category: class_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: PatternError.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["PatternError"]
  expected: true

invariant re_extra47.PatternError_qualname_eq:
  description: "re.PatternError.__qualname__ == 'PatternError' — qualname equals name for top-level classes; novel equality anchor via PatternError attribute path in re_extra47; verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0"
  category: class_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: PatternError.__qualname__.__eq__
  args: ["PatternError"]
  expected: true

invariant re_extra47.PatternError_module_eq:
  description: "re.PatternError.__module__ == 're' — PatternError is defined in the re module; no prior re spec checks PatternError.__module__; novel equality anchor in re_extra47; verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0"
  category: class_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: PatternError.__module__.__eq__
  args: ["re"]
  expected: true

invariant re_extra47.PatternError_base_name_eq:
  description: "re.PatternError.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'Exception' — PatternError inherits directly from Exception; re_extra21 covers this via re.error alias; novel anchor via PatternError attribute path in re_extra47; verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0"
  category: class_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "PatternError.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__"
  args: ["Exception"]
  expected: true

invariant re_extra47.PatternError_mro_len:
  description: "re.PatternError.__mro__.__len__() == 4 — MRO is [PatternError, Exception, BaseException, object]; re_extra13 covers re.error.mro().__len__()==4 via .mro() method; this anchors via .__mro__.__len__() dunder path; novel dunder anchor in re_extra47; verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0"
  category: class_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: PatternError.__mro__.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 4
